pr_review_body:
@tkazik , thank you for the contribution.
Can you restructure the PR so that the editorial and content changes will be captured in separate commits for review?
Thanks

I left some initial comments; 

High level comment is; 

- The manager class APIs seem a bit brittle (especially with cache). Can we clean this up with ABCClass? I also think we should hide cache behind the manager's create/delete APIs.
- Cache means the agent becomes stateful, which means the behavior after agent restarts is undefined. Is there a design for how to handle this? Also, if we don't handle this right now, can we make this feature off by default? We shouldn't have non-fully working feature just for the sake of performance optimization, especially when the feature is already GA'ed

Looks good in general.
@webknjaz please feel free to merge when ready.
I think the PR can be backported to 3.7 branch (label + bot works fine)

@adamnovak  I tried reviewing, but then I got confused by the missing and unchecked types; so I started fixing the types.

https://github.com/DataBiosphere/toil/commit/509562ec54da3b4f310f567a94356ab4158703be

However I've run out of time for today. I'll try again tomorrow.
